<p>Taking the top spot for the best home gym overall is the Force USA G12 All-In-One Trainer. It offers the best versatility out of our top ten choices and comes with a ton of extra attachments. While it represents a significant investment, it provides a full-body workout using a fairly small footprint for what it offers.</p>



<p>Buying this unit gives you access to a functional trainer, smith machine, cable machine, and vertical leg press. The dual 200-pound weight stacks offer a 1:1 ratio. This means that you’re getting a higher maximum weight with bigger increments.</p>



<p>The 2″ x 2″ uprights use 1″ holes with laser-cut numbers. This does limit you in terms of attachment options but it shouldn’t matter with the range already included.</p>



<p>One of the great things about the G12 trainer is the six-weight storage pins and vertical barbell holder. You also have several hooks in the center to store the attachments.</p>



<p>With so many uses, the G12 takes a bit of knowledge to assemble correctly. Because of this, you can pay for someone to do it or watch an online video.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Overall, the G12 does everything well and offers a huge range of uses. It has clever storage and an integrated Smith machine. With this, it’s our top pick option.</strong></p>



