<p>The Bells Of Steel All-In-One Home Gym uses a simple but compact design that offers a lot for a smaller piece of kit. You basically have a functional trainer and cable machine with clever integrated plate storage in the middle.&nbsp;</p>



<p>A particularly great feature of the Bells Of Steel Gym is that the uprights double as a squat stand. All you need is some J-Cups and a barbell. Furthermore, you have the option to add additional attachments such as a dip station.</p>



<p>The side cable pulleys use a 2:1 pull ratio which means they use half the resistance to what’s shown. This makes them great for smaller isolation-type exercises. In the middle, you have a 1:1 pull ratio that can be used for heavier movements.</p>



<p>At 54.6″L x 59″W x 81″H, it’s definitely one of the most compact machines on our list. It uses an X-frame design that should fit nicely into a corner or smaller gym space.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Each unit includes two nylon handles, a lat pulldown bar, and a short straight bar. One thing to bear in mind is that you need to bolt it down to use it safely. If you can’t do this then consider the other options on our list.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Overall, the Bells Of Steel Trainer offers a compact, functional gym with multiple attachment options. It also comes at a great price point for what it offers.&nbsp;</strong></p>



