<p>Last on our list we have the NordicTrack Fusion CST Studio With Rower. Take one look at it and you’ll probably say we’ve saved the best till last. It uses a futuristic design to give you a modern take on a traditional home gym.</p>



<p>It&#8217;s a technology-driven home gym with a small footprint and a cool-looking design. It builds on the rise of <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10525173/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">integrated technology</a> being used for fitness training and equipment.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The Fusion CST has a built-in 10-inch touchscreen allowing you to stream workout videos as you use it. The integrated iFit technology means a trainer can provide you with on-demand form feedback and adjust your workout. This means it’s a great option for beginners or those who prefer more workout guidance.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It has 20 levels of magnetic resistance which gives you 20–200 of total resistance. This should be enough for beginners and most intermediate athletes.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The six cable anchor points provide plenty of exercise angle options. The rower is also a great addition as it allows you to mix in some cardio training. However, future models could look to add more exercise options such as a pull-up bar or integrated free weights.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Overall, the Fusion CST is a modern home gym solution with clever integrated technology. It’s a significant investment but does a lot of things that normal gyms can’t.</strong></p>



